"{\"uid\": \"dailytrust.com-covid-19-looms-over-olympics-with-several-athletes-testing-positive\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  Three years after the Tokyo Olympics were held amid strict precautions and with no fans because of the global COVID-19 pandemic, there is now another fear of the disease in Paris.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 181, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 175, \"end\": 180, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999230562965, \"rank\": 7.694369097758241e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The virus has forced athletes to withdraw from events at the Paris Games and has others donning masks again.\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 291, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This time the impact is much more limited though.\", \"from\": 293, \"to\": 342, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Several athletes have tested positive, including Australian swimmer Lani Pallister.\", \"from\": 344, \"to\": 427, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 393, \"end\": 403, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9780708974488622, \"rank\": 0.021122239241370654, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 412, \"end\": 426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lani_Pallister\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lani Pallister\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lani_Pallister\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lani_Pallister\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She was a medal hope in the women's 1500 metres freestyle but had to withdraw from the event.\", \"from\": 429, \"to\": 522, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A team spokeswoman said, however, that the decision was made to save Pallister's energy for the 4x200m freestyle relay which starts on Thursday.\", \"from\": 524, \"to\": 668, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Likewise, British swimmer Adam Peaty, tested positive a day after he just missed out on 100m breaststroke gold, sharing silver with American Nic Fink.\", \"from\": 670, \"to\": 820, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 680, \"end\": 687, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.8705125732710549, \"rank\": 0.1486690492660478, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 696, \"end\": 706, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Adam Peaty\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\"}, {\"begin\": 802, \"end\": 810, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.994537728320438, \"rank\": 0.005412498198172654, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 811, \"end\": 819, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nic_Fink\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nic Fink\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nic_Fink\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nic_Fink\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has now said he would focus on a \\\"fast, full recovery\\\" to give his best in relays later in the week.\", \"from\": 822, \"to\": 925, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Several Australian women's water polo players tested positive for COVID-19 in the days leading up to the opening ceremony, forcing them to isolate themselves from other team members.\", \"from\": 927, \"to\": 1109, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 935, \"end\": 945, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9780708974488622, \"rank\": 0.021122239241370654, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 993, \"end\": 1001, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19\", \"score\": 0.9995336419006081, \"rank\": 0.00046580003128264167, \"text\": \"COVID-19\", \"types\": [\"Q12136\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However the team played on Tuesday, smashing Serbia 8-3.\", \"from\": 1111, \"to\": 1167, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Tokyo Games were delayed a year due to COVID while the 2022 Beijing Winter Olympics were held with strict precautions, making Paris the first post-pandemic Olympics.\", \"from\": 1169, \"to\": 1338, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1299, \"end\": 1304, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999230562965, \"rank\": 7.694369097758241e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are no strict protocols or restrictions around COVID-19 in Paris.\", \"from\": 1340, \"to\": 1411, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1393, \"end\": 1401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19\", \"score\": 0.9995336419006081, \"rank\": 0.00046580003128264167, \"text\": \"COVID-19\", \"types\": [\"Q12136\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19\"}, {\"begin\": 1405, \"end\": 1410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999230562965, \"rank\": 7.694369097758241e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resourc